Q1. Write a python program to accept a string, extract all words that start with a capital letter and remove all special characters from a string. Display modified string. (Accept input from user)

import re
s = input("Enter a string: ")
clean = re.sub(r'[^A-Za-z0-9 ]', '', s)
words = clean.split()
cap_words = [w for w in words if w[0].isupper()]
print("Words starting with capital letters:", cap_words)
print("Modified string:", clean)


Q2. Create a Web Page using Flask which contains following information about your Library Book List
a) Show the library name as a heading.
b) Display all available books in a table with title and author.
c) Add quote about reading in bold and blue color.


from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    library_name = "My Library"

    books = [
        ("Python Basics", "John Smith"),
        ("Data Science", "Alice Brown"),
        ("Machine Learning", "David Lee")
    ]

    # Build table rows manually
    rows = ""
    for title, author in books:
        rows += f"<tr><td>{title}</td><td>{author}</td></tr>"

    html = f"""
    <html>
    <head><title>Library</title></head>
    <body>

    <h1>{library_name}</h1>

    <table border="1">
        <tr><th>Title</th><th>Author</th></tr>
        {rows}
    </table>

    <p style="color:blue; font-weight:bold;">
        A room without books is like a body without a soul.
    </p>

    </body>
    </html>
    """

    return html

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=True)



